		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Poe Ballantine</span></strong>&rsquo;s novel <em>Decline of the Lawrence Welk Empire</em> will be published in July by Hawthorne Books. His piece in this issue is nonfiction. &ldquo;I hate to fictionalize true material,&rdquo; he writes. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m arrogant about having taken risks in life and working with my hands instead of sitting in some teachers&rsquo; lounge contemplating the snack machines.&rdquo; He lives in Chadron, Nebraska.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


